snippet.textDisplay:
You can’t be the “greatest” to ever play for a franchise when you bail on them after a close loss in a conference final to the team that beat you.

That’s not “greatness”. Greatness in sports is synonymous with grit. It’s why Lebrons and Wades championships apart are both considered greater than anything they won together. And why Jordan personified greatness with the flu game, multiple years falling short to the Pistons to finally break through, or playing through the Knicks “Jordan rules” and still winning.

Nothing KD will ever do is going to compare to those moments. Dudes a gutless front runner. He’s all world generational talent but he’s not a champion the way the greats that came before him are.

Sorry KD fans. That’s the narrative and there is no changing that.
